quran[21]{c,v,t,f}:
44,19,"and do not exalt yourselves in defiance of Allah. I have come to you with a clear authority {1} (as a Messenger).",footnotes:1:In other words
44,20,"I have taken refuge with my Lord and your Lord lest you should attack me with stones."
44,21,"But if you do not believe what I say, leave me alone {1} (and desist from laying hands on me).”",footnotes:1:This was said at the time when
44,22,"Then he called upon his Lord: “These are a criminal people.” {1}",footnotes:1:This is the final report that the Prophet Moses (peace be upon him) presented before his Lord
44,23,"(He was told): “Set out with My servants by night {1} for you will certainly be pursued. {2}",footnotes:1:With my servants: With all those people who have believed
44,24,"And leave the sea behind you as calm as ever. Surely they are an army that is doomed to be drowned.” {1}",footnotes:1:This command was given when the Prophet Moses (peace be upon him) had crossed the sea along with his caravan and wanted that he should restore the sea to its former state by smiting it with the staff so that Pharaoh and his hosts should not pursue them on the dry path created by the miracle. At that times it was said: Leave the sea divided as it is
44,25,"How many gardens did they leave behind, and how many fountains"
44,26,"and sown fields and splendid mansions,"
44,27,"and the life of ease in which they took delight!"
44,28,"Thus it was; and We made another people inherit all that. {1}",footnotes:1:Hasan Basri says that “other people” here implies the children of Israel
44,29,"Then neither the sky shed tears over them nor the earth. {1} They were granted no respite.",footnotes:1:That is
44,30,"Thus did We deliver the Children of Israel from the humiliating chastisement,"
44,31,"from Pharaoh {1} who was most prominent among the prodigals. {2}",footnotes:1:That is
44,32,"We knowingly exalted them (i.e., the Children of Israel) above other peoples of the world {1}",footnotes:1:That is
44,33,"and bestowed upon them the Signs wherein lay an evident test for them. {1}",footnotes:1:For explanation
44,34,"Indeed these people say:"
44,35,"“This is our first and only death, and we shall never be raised again. {1}",footnotes:1:That is
44,36,"Bring back to us our fathers if you are truthful.” {1}",footnotes:1:This was their reasoning: We have never seen a dead person resurrected to life. Therefore
44,37,"Are these better or the people of Tubba {1} and those who went before them? We destroyed them for they were a criminal people. {2}",footnotes:1:Tubba was the title of the kings of the Himyarites
44,38,"It was not in idle sport that We created the heavens and the earth and all that is between them."
44,39,"We did not create them except in Truth. But most of them do not know. {1}",footnotes:1:This is the second answer to their objection; it means: Whoever denies life after death and the rewards and punishments of the hereafter
(	Surah Al-Muminun, Ayat 115); (Surah Ar-Room,"Ayats 8-9 )and the corresponding E.Ns)."
